    </ol>
    <ol class="numberText" start="4"  type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;">
        <li style="margin-top:14pt; margin-left:59pt;  line-height:normal; padding-left:13pt; font-family:Roboto; font-size:13.5pt; background-color:#ffffff;"><strong>PARTNER COMMISSIONS AND PAYMENT TERMS</strong>
    
    
    
        <ol type="i" class="awlist1 small-roman" style="margin-right:0pt; margin-left:0pt; padding-left:0pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;">
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong> Partner Commissions.</strong>  Once a Retailer is onboarded on the packaging Depot Store Platform, The Partner shall be eligible for commission on all Purchases made on the packaging Depot Store Platform by the said Retailer after being onboarded by the Partner, except for Purchases made by the said Retailers from Sellers with whom the said Retailers have an Existing Business Relationship prior to the Said Retailer being onboarded on the packaging Depot Store Platform.</p></li>
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Payment terms.</strong> </p>
                <ol class="lower-alpha" type="a" class="awlist1" style="margin-right:0pt; margin-left:0pt; padding-left:0pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;">
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>Partner Commission shall be based on the percentage of Net Value of the Purchases (Net Value shall be Purchase Cost exclusive of Taxes, Logistic Charges, Discounts and any Schemes) made by the Retailers, onboarded on the platform by the Business Associate. Partner Commission is based on the rates as set forth in the Business Associate Program.</p></li>
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>Partner Commission shall become due only once 15 days have passed from the expiry of the Return Period.</p></li>
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>Payment of the Partner Commission shall be made by Bank transfer subject to deduction of Direct and Indirect Taxes.</p></li>
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>Due Commission Shall be paid to the Partners post reduction of recoveries, if any from the Partner.</p></li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong> Taxes.</strong>  The Business Associate will bear all taxes and duties which may be levied with respect to the payment of the Partner Commission by packaging Depot Store.</p></li>
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong> Expenses.</strong>  The Business Associate will bear all expenses and travel costs it may incur with respect to the performance of this Agreement.</p></li>
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong> Currency.</strong>  All payments shall be made in the INR by packaging Depot Store to the Business Associates.</p></li>
        </ol>
        </li>
        </ol>


        <ol class="numberText" start="5"  type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;">
            <li style="margin-top:14pt; margin-left:59pt;  line-height:normal; padding-left:13pt; font-family:Roboto; font-size:13.5pt; background-color:#ffffff;"><strong>INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS, OWNERSHIP AND TITLE</strong>
        
        
        
            <ol type="i" class="awlist1 small-roman" style="margin-right:0pt; margin-left:0pt; padding-left:0pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;">
                <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Ownership.</strong>   packaging Depot Store retains all right, title, and interest in and to the Services (and any copies thereof), and in all related copyrights, trade secrets, patents, trademarks, and any other intellectual and industrial property and proprietary rights, including registrations, applications, renewals, and extensions of such rights. The Business Associate is not granted any rights to any trademarks or service marks of packaging Depot Store. The Business Associate hereby assigns all necessary rights, title, and interest necessary to accomplish the foregoing ownership.</p></li>
                <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong> Use of Trademarks/Trade Names.</strong></p>
                    <ol class="lower-alpha" type="a" class="awlist1" style="margin-right:0pt; margin-left:0pt; padding-left:0pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;">
                        <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Trademarks. </strong>   During the Term of this Agreement, Business Associate shall have the right to advertise the Services under packaging Depot Store trademarks, marks, and trade names and in the promotion and distribution of the Services. In addition, the Business Associate shall fully comply with all reasonable guidelines, if any, communicated by packaging Depot Store concerning the use of packaging Depot Store’S trademarks.</p></li>
                        <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>The Business Associate shall not alter or remove any of packaging Depot Store’S trademarks affixed to the Services by packaging Depot Store. Except as set forth in this Section 6.2, nothing contained in this Agreement shall grant or shall be deemed to grant to the Business Associate any right, title or interest in or to packaging Depot Store’s trademarks. All uses of packaging Depot Store's trademarks shall inure solely to the benefit of packaging Depot Store and Business Associate shall obtain no rights with respect to any of packaging Depot Store's trademarks, other than the right to market and promote the Services as set forth herein, and Business Associate irrevocably assigns to packaging Depot Store all such right, title and interest, if any, in any of packaging Depot Store’S trademarks. At no time during or after the term of this Agreement shall the Business Associate challenge or assist others to challenge packaging Depot Store’S trademarks or the registration thereof or attempt to register any trademarks, marks or trade names confusingly similar to those of packaging Depot Store Upon termination of this Agreement, Business Associate shall immediately cease to use all of packaging Depot Store’S trademarks. packaging Depot Store shall not use name, logo, and brand name of the Business Associate, without Business Associate’s prior written approval.</p></li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <ol class="numberText" start="6"  type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;">
        <li style="margin-top:14pt; margin-left:59pt;  line-height:normal; padding-left:13pt; font-family:Roboto; font-size:13.5pt; background-color:#ffffff;"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY</strong>
    
    
    
        <ol type="i" class="awlist1 small-roman" style="margin-right:0pt; margin-left:0pt; padding-left:0pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;">
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Use and Disclosure.</strong> During this Agreement and for a period of five (5) years following its termination, each Party shall hold in confidence and not use or disclose to any third party any Confidential Information of the other Party. Each Party agrees to take all reasonable steps to ensure that the Confidential Information is not disclosed or distributed by its employees, contractors or agents in violation of the terms of this Agreement.</p></li>
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Permitted Disclosures.</strong> Either Party may disclose Confidential Information of the other Party either</p>
                <ol class="lower-alpha" type="a" class="awlist1" style="margin-right:0pt; margin-left:0pt; padding-left:0pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;">
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>in response to a valid order by a court or other governmental or regulatory body,</p></li>
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>as otherwise required by law, or</p></li>
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>as necessary to establish the rights of either Party under this Agreement; provided such Party promptly notifies the other Party of such request and allows it the opportunity to object or to seek a protective order.</p></li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Non-Confidential Information.</strong> The Parties shall not be obligated under this <strong>“Confidentiality”</strong> clause with respect to Confidential Information that:</p>
                <ol class="lower-alpha" type="a" class="awlist1" style="margin-right:0pt; margin-left:0pt; padding-left:0pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;">
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>is or becomes a part of the public domain through no act or omission of the receiving Party;</p></li>
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>was in the receiving Party’s lawful possession without restriction prior to the disclosure and had not been obtained by the receiving Party either directly or indirectly from the disclosing Party;</p></li>
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>is lawfully disclosed to the receiving Party by a third party without restriction on the disclosure; or</p></li>
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>is independently developed by the receiving Party without access to the Confidential Information</p></li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Destruction or Return.</strong> Except as otherwise authorized or required in furtherance of the purposes of this Agreement, promptly upon a request by the disclosing Party, the receiving Party will destroy (and so certify in writing) or return to the disclosing Party all Confidential Information and all documents or media containing any such Confidential Information and all copies or extracts thereof, provided that the receiving Party shall be permitted to retain copies of any computer records and files containing any Confidential Information which have been created pursuant to automatic archiving and back-up procedures, or retain a back-up copy of such Confidential Information as required by law, rule, regulation or internal compliance policies, in which cases such Confidential Information shall continue to be subject to confidentiality obligations even after termination of this Agreement.</p></li>
        </ol>
    </li>
    </ol>

    <ol class="numberText" start="7"  type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;">
        <li style="margin-top:14pt; margin-left:59pt;  line-height:normal; padding-left:13pt; font-family:Roboto; font-size:13.5pt; background-color:#ffffff;"><strong>TERM AND TERMINATION</strong>
    
    
    
        <ol type="i" class="awlist1 small-roman" style="margin-right:0pt; margin-left:0pt; padding-left:0pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;">
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Term of Agreement.</strong> The Term of this Agreement will be for one years from the date of CP Registration Approval by packaging Depot Store. This Agreement may be renewed for successive one-year terms by both parties agreeing in writing to such renewal until the termination date. Notwithstanding the foregoing, packaging Depot Store reserves the right to modify or amend the Business Associate Program from time to time. packaging Depot Store shall notify the Business Associate of such modifications or amendments to Business Associate Program. If any such modification or amendment to the Business Associate Program is unacceptable to Business Associate, Business Associate’s sole and exclusive remedy shall be to terminate this Agreement within thirty (30) days after such modification.</p></li>
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Immediate Termination.</strong> Either Party may immediately terminate the Agreement in cases of material breach of this Agreement by the other Party. In cases of exceptional circumstances either Party may evoke such termination, for:</p>
                <ol class="lower-alpha" type="a" class="awlist1" style="margin-right:0pt; margin-left:0pt; padding-left:0pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;">
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>bankruptcy;</p></li>
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>death, retirement, illness, or incapacity of the other Party or key personnel and</p></li>
                    <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p>the acceptance of bribes and/or conviction for any criminal offence.</p></li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Termination for Convenience. </strong>Either Party may terminate the Agreement, for any reason or no reason, and without any liability towards the other Party, by giving the other Party a thirty (30) day prior written notice.</p></li>
