        <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Audits.</strong> During the term of this Agreement and for a period of 5 years following its termination, Business Associate shall maintain and not delete books and records regarding this Agreement and/or Services. packaging Depot Store may, through quality audits, inspect and audit the other Party’s records to verify compliance with the rights and obligations under this agreement. Such audit may only occur once a year, following fifteen (15) business days prior written notice to the Business Associate. All costs in relation to any audit shall be borne by packaging Depot Store. Parties agree to cooperate with the audit and provide packaging Depot Store with reasonable assistance and access to information. Any audit shall be performed during normal working hours in such a manner as to not interfere with the operations of the Business Associate being audited. An audit shall not include access to internal policies, IT-systems or any other information not relating directly to the Agreement and/or Services.</p>
        </li>
        <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Engagement of third parties by Business Associate.</strong> The Business Associate may not appoint or engage third parties in relation to this Agreement without the prior written consent of packaging Depot Store</p>
        </li>
        <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>Severability.</strong> If for any reason a court of competent jurisdiction finds any provision of this Agreement, or portion thereof, to be unenforceable, that provision of the Agreement will be enforced to the maximum extent permissible so as to affect the intent of the Parties, and the remainder of this Agreement will continue in full force and effect.</p>
        </li>
        <li style="margin-left:31.65pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:normal; background-color:#ffffff;"><p><strong>No Waiver of Rights.</strong> The failure of either Party to enforce any of the provisions of this Agreement, or the failure to require performance by the other Party of any of the provisions of this Agreement, shall not be construed to be a present or future waiver of such provisions, nor affect the validity of either Party’s right to enforce such provision in future.</p>
